        "One new thing you'll see here is the `ngram`: ngrams are 'simply' pairs, or triplets, or quadruplets of words. You may come across the terms unigram (`ngram(1,1)`), bigram (`ngram(2,2)`), trigram (`ngram(3,3)`)... typically, you will rarely find anything beyond trigrams, and these present real issues for text2vec algorithms because the embedding for `geographical`, `information`, and `systems` is _not_ the same as for `geographical information systetms`.\n",
